# React Components

Keep components under 200 lines. Use Zustand for state management. Extract logic into custom hooks.

Usage examples:

- `function UserCard({ userId }: { userId: string }): JSX.Element`
- `const user = useUserStore(state => state.getUser(userId))`
- `const Component = memo(({ data }: Props) => <div>{data}</div>)`
- Use useCallback for event handlers passed to child components
- Use useMemo for expensive calculations: `const expensiveValue = useMemo(() => computeValue(data), [data])`
- Extract complex logic: `const { items, loading, error } = useItemsLogic(userId)`
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Use React.forwardRef for ref forwarding
